summary: Arya rose, carrots dangling from her hand. It sounded like the singer was coming up the river road. Over among the cabbages, Hot...
text: Arya rose, carrots dangling from her hand. It sounded like the singer was coming up the river road. Over among the cabbages, Hot Pie had heard it too, to judge by the look on his face. Gendry had gone to sleep in the shade of the burned cottage, and was past hearing anything. […] "Go wake Gendry,“ Arya told him. "Just shake him by the shoulder, don’t make a lot of noise.” Gendry was easy to wake, unlike Hot Pie, who needed to be kicked and shouted at.

Arya: Where's Jaqen? I need him!
Gendry: You need him?!
Arya: Please don’t tell me that your hopeless infatuation is devolving into pointless jealousy.
Gendry: No, I’m not jealous, I’m just a little concerned for you. I didn’t like the look of that guy.
Arya: Because he looked better than you?
Gendry: Yeah. He was kinda dreamy.

summary: Post canon-hc 3/∞ ?
body:
Post canon-hc 3/∞ ?

As a surprise on year, Arya decides to take Gendry to Qohor to see the ancient forges. It’s months before he finally stops talking her ear off about it once they arrive back home, and several more before they welcome their first born into the world. For all his stubborn brooding before, Arya has never seen him so happy in all her life.

summary: I've begun to think by then end one of the Stark girls will likely have to marry into Dorne, most likely to Trystane Martell. (I...
question: I've begun to think by then end one of the Stark girls will likely have to marry into Dorne, most likely to Trystane Martell. (I don't think the any of the Seven Kingdoms will have independence at the series end, it's more a question of making staying together appealing.) While more of Sansa's plot is about being prepared for a political marriage, Arya would be a better fit for moving to Dorne. As someone who wants something of a happy ending for both, I can't really reconcile this. Thoughts?
answer:
I…don’t see it. I think the end of the series puts the surviving Starklings in a position where they get to decide their own destinies to a much greater extent. Sansa, who’s spent most of the series having other people decide for her who she’s going to marry, is going to end up being able to pick a partner for herself. Arya, who’s spent most of the series utterly opposed to being shoved in a box where the only viable option for her future is marriage and living vicariously through husband and sons, is going to end up being able to pick a partner for herself. 

Whether or not they actually do this on-page is another matter.

I’m not sure how the fate of Dorne gets tied up in story either, but I hope it’s with at least some of the justice Doran wants. That, I think, is the most important regional plot point. Sure I hope that the surviving Starks and Martells can be friends and allies, but I don’t see it as a dramatic necessity.
